 Used to divide playbooks into directory structure 
 we can organize the playbook
Reduce the playbook length 

CREATING ROLE 1 (TO PERFORM TASK 1) 

mkdir playbooks

 cd playbooks

 yum install tree -y
 
 mkdir -p roles/one/tasks

 vim roles/one/tasks/main.yml


- name: installing httpd
  yum:                  # Aligned vertically with 'name'
    name: httpd
    state: present


 vim master.yml

- hosts: all
  roles:
    - one


# tree
.
├── master.yml
└── roles
    └── one
        └── tasks
            └── main.yml



 cat master.yml

 cat roles/one/tasks/main.yml

ansible-playbook master.yml -b





CREATING ROLE TWO  (To perform task 2)


 mkdir -p roles/two/tasks

 vim roles/two/tasks/main.yml

 tree


.
├── master.yml
└── roles
    ├── one
    │   └── tasks
    │       └── main.yml
    └── two
        └── tasks
            └── main.yml



 vim master.yml 

Add -two

- hosts: all
  roles:
    - one
    - two






ansible-playbook master.yml -b



TO REMOVE PACKAGES and USERS

All files are located in folder "playbooks" 

Run:

tree



 cd playbooks 

sed -i 's/present/absent/g' roles/one/tasks/main.yml

 cat roles/one/tasks/main.yml

ansible-playbook master.yml -b


To remove user task 2

sed -i 's/present/absent/g' roles/two/tasks/main.yml

 cat roles/two/tasks/main.yml


ansible-playbook master.yml -b




To remove the entire folder 

 rm -r playbooks

Keep pressing y
